cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

The paper proposes a new approach for Neural Architecture Search (NAS) that can be useful for different domains beyond image classification of natural images. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer architecture (cs.AR). Among these, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely categories as the paper focuses on optimizing neural network architecture for image classification tasks and proposes a new approach for NAS.
